the first applicant (the "cepu"), craig brown and david coombs contend that the dismissal of each employee occurred in contravention of s 792(1)(a) of the workplace relations act 1996 (cth) ("the act") because, they say, blue star dismissed each employee for the reason that, or for reasons that included as an operative reason, that each employee had given evidence before the federal court of australia in proceedings commenced by the cepu contesting whether a proposed employee collective agreement between blue star and its employees ("the proposed blue star agreement") had been approved in accordance with the requirements of s 340 of the act and particularly s 340(2) of the act.